HEADWORD: Driftway
<hw>Drift"way`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
common way, road, or path, for driving cattle.</def> <rj><au>Cowell.
Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mining)</fld> <def>Same as <er>Drift</er>,
<er>11</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Driftweed</ent>⟦br⟧
